# Quantis Tracking Rules

Quantis tracks WHAT is being built and WHERE the project stands, in `.quantis/`. HOW things get built comes from installed methodology skills (superpowers, Cursor Plan Mode, …). `/q-next` conducts: it reads the state, routes to the right skill, and records the outcome.

## The two files

- **`.quantis/ROADMAP.md`** — durable truth. Intent header (Vision, Non-Goals, Success Criteria, `Status: DRAFT|FINALIZED`), phases, decisions. Schema:

  ```markdown
  ### Phase {N}: {name}
  Status: ⬜ | 🔄 | ✅
  Objective: {what this phase delivers}
  Spec: {path/to/design.md — optional, from the brainstorming/design step}
  Plan: {path/to/plan.md, once planned}
  Gaps: {only after a failed verification}
  ```

  Edit it in place — update the milestone line, append phases, never regenerate the file. Roadmap edits (add/remove/reorder phases) need no special command; do them when asked, keeping the schema.

- **`.quantis/STATE.md`** — session memory. Current position, session summary, context dump, next steps. Update it as work happens, not just at `/q-pause`. Durable decisions go in ROADMAP's Decisions section, not here.

## Gates

- **Planning Lock**: no implementation code while the ROADMAP header says `Status: DRAFT` or `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION]` markers remain.
- **Evidence or it didn't happen**: a phase becomes ✅ only via `.quantis/phases/{N}-{slug}/VERIFICATION.md` containing `verdict: PASS` with empirical proof (command output, test results, screenshots — never "looks correct"). Checked-off plan tasks alone don't complete a phase.

## Working with methodology plugins

- **Link, don't relocate.** Tools keep their artifact homes (superpowers: `docs/superpowers/specs|plans/`; Plan Mode: `.cursor/plans/`; others: their defaults). ROADMAP phase entries carry `Plan: {path}` links. `.quantis/phases/` holds only verification evidence.
- **Don't duplicate task tracking — and read the plugin's real signals.** The plugin owns tasks/steps/checkboxes; Quantis tracks phase-level status only. A phase counts as build-complete on ANY of: the SDD ledger (`.superpowers/sdd/progress.md`) showing all plan tasks done, git showing the work merged/landed, or all plan checkboxes ticked. Superpowers SDD never ticks plan checkboxes — never treat unticked boxes alone as "not built".
- **Precedence while a `q-*` skill runs**: auto-invoked plugin skills are sub-procedures — their output feeds the Quantis artifact, and they cannot skip the Planning Lock, skip verification, jump ahead a stage, or move Quantis files. Afterwards, plugins behave normally.
- **One tracking layer only.** Never pair Quantis with plugins that are themselves tracking systems (Spec Kit, Taskmaster, OpenSpec, memory-bank) — one owner for project state.

## Commits

`type(scope): description` (feat/fix/docs/refactor/test/chore; scope = `phase-N` for phase work). After each commit, confirm it succeeded (`git log -1`); on hook rejection fix and re-commit (never `--no-verify`); mid-merge/rebase or detached HEAD → stop and ask.

## Session hygiene

After 3 failed debugging attempts: dump state (`/q-pause`) and start a fresh session. If context is degrading (20+ tool calls, re-reading known files, context warnings), snapshot STATE.md before anything else.
